The paper discusses a framework for hyperparameter tuning in machine learning classifiers using Bayesian optimization and statistical learning theory. The most relevant sub-category for this paper is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as it directly deals with optimizing machine learning models. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). These sub-categories are likely because the paper discusses tuning hyperparameters for various machine learning algorithms, which are commonly used in these fields.
